  <brief_title>Spirituality, Religiosity, and Immune Functioning</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>National Center for Complementary and Integrative Health (NCCIH)</agency>
      <agency_class>NIH</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>National Center for Complementary and Integrative Health (NCCIH)</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether religiosity and spirituality are related to
      immune functioning, as measured by interleukin-6 blood plasma level, among terminally ill
      cancer patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
